f:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Pipefy is best suited for HR teams, procurement, service management, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Rossum, meanwhile, shines for enterprises, logistics, supply chain, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2014, Pipefy describes itself as \"AI-enhanced business process automation with customizable workflows.\" Rossum, established in 2017, positions itself as \"AI document understanding platform for enterprise data capture.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
10:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Rossum** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to more features (10 vs 9). However, this does not mean Pipefy is a poor choice — far from it. Pipefy excels in its own right, particularly for HR teams and procurement.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value high accuracy on structured documents, go with Rossum. If excellent pipe/kanban workflow model matters more to you, Pipefy is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
